<rss xmlns:taxo="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/taxonomy/" xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" version="2.0">
  <channel>
    <title>Top 10</title>
    <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=monkbalance&amp;message.id=10769</link>
    <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;OK, I've finally moved house (all 6000 or so miles from the UK to Toronto) &amp;amp; am about 200 boxes unpacked of 300, so have now got some time to go back over the beta top 10 list and reformat it. I'd like to try and get this submitted before the next deadline Kyth sets if possible. It's not hugely different than the 1st draft, but I've made several changes I hope that incorproate most of the feedback from the first post as well as some additional changes given what we've had happen in PoR (ie, Aura's), and some statements from the recent FF (ie, no chance of an END based fade/ID).&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;I'll be asking for a poll on acceptance of this list on this board when Kyth is back and recovered from the Fan Fair.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;1. Riposte “Immunity”&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some form of riposte immunity&lt;/strong&gt; - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;font color="#ff3300"&gt;&lt;span&gt;No development feedback at this time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Given &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;SoE’s&lt;/span&gt; oft stated, “damage from any angle” role for monks, this is not possible because attacking from the front can result in taking serious damage or even death due to ripostes. Monks get a lot of strikethrough (via items, and 2 AA lines), however the mob still gets “an attack” when you “strike through” a riposte, and if it hits you still take damage. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;An AA line to give a chance of immunity to ripostes&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;An AA line to tie in Strikethrough to riposte immunity so that if you strike through an opponents attack, you do NOT take riposte damage&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;These &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;AAs&lt;/span&gt; would only work when NOT top of the agro list&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;These AA’s would not work against ENRAGE&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Fix strikethrough so that you do not get riposted when you strikethrough a riposte&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr size="2" width="100%"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt; 2. Monk Relative DPS &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;vs&lt;/span&gt; other DPS classes&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An update on the class re-balancing of DPS (“round 2”)&lt;/strong&gt; - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;font color="#cc0000"&gt;&lt;span&gt;DPS evaluation for all classes has begun and will be the focus of part #2 of the class Re-Envision process&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Monks being one of the DPS classes, [ we feel ] are slightly unbalanced in our relative DPS given like-for-like AA/itemisation against the other melee and casting “DPS” classes, and the inherent risks we take as a melee class (&lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;ie&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;AoE&lt;/span&gt; rampage, ripostes, mobs moving/OOR etc). We’d like to see the results of the DPS re-evaluation “round 2” mentioned many times, and as part of this;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Further evaluation of current monk special attacks.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr size="2" width="100%"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;3. Itemisation&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Item weight is carefully considered with the monk weight limit in mind. Items that are “leather class” based should be considered carefully with monks weight limit in mind, as Druids and &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;Beastlords&lt;/span&gt; do not have the same weight limitation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Currently the biggest issue monks have with itemisation is the weight of items. Many items are far too heavy for monks (&lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;&lt;span class="GramE"&gt;esp&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; low level monks), even some monk specific items.&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;Additionally;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Continuation of the “pouches” (summoned throwing items) introduced with &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;DoDH&lt;/span&gt; in future expansions. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Careful consideration of the focus effects on future sets of monk armour. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;A further line of player made throwing items (cf. Javelins), &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;ie&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;shurikens&lt;/span&gt;. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;More “robe” BP graphics for those who wish to see robes. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;&lt;span&gt;More “leather” graphics for those who wish to see the “leather” look - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr size="2" width="100%"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;4. EMPTY&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;This item is currently empty (was innate run speed).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr size="2" width="100%"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;5. Mend Improvements&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An AA to reduce the refresh timer on MEND&lt;/strong&gt; -&lt;font color="#ff3300"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;font color="#cc0000"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Mend has been in the game, unchanged since day one except for the critical mend line that came in when AA’s were first introduced. Whilst a 25% base (50% &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;crit&lt;/span&gt; via AA) mend is useful, in today’s game with trash mobs that hit for over 10% of your &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;HP’s&lt;/span&gt; PER HIT, we feel it’s time the mend skill got a little additional help beyond the current “critical mend” AA we have.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Have the &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;tickdown&lt;/span&gt; timer on MEND showing how long to refresh once used like other hot keys (&lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;ie&lt;/span&gt;, Dragon Fang).&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Add a new AA: Hastened Mend (N levels, X percent reduction in timer per level, &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;ie&lt;/span&gt;, 5 levels, 6 % per level, down to 4:12 &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;mins&lt;/span&gt; )&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr size="2" width="100%"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;6. EMPTY&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;This item is currently empty (was Leather graphics, now integrated into item 3)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr size="2" width="100%"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;7. Disc stacking&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Earthwalk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt; (&amp;amp; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;Stonestance&lt;/span&gt;) should be on it’s own timer (not on the &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;Voiddance&lt;/span&gt;/Whirlwind timer)&lt;/strong&gt; - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;font color="#cc0000"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Several of the monk disciplines are on the same timer, and in some cases this is overly detrimental, especially when discs now cost END to use so cannot be chained. Using &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;Voiddance&lt;/span&gt; (a level 54 disc) currently disables &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;Earthwalk&lt;/span&gt; (a 65 disc) for 40 &lt;span class="GramE"&gt;minutes !.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Throw Stone should be on different timer than Lulls &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Dragon Fang should be on a different timer than Lulls&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr size="2" width="100%"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;8. Weight Limit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An actual benefit for being under weight&lt;/strong&gt; - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;font color="#cc0000"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Currently there is no benefit for being “under weight”, only a penalty for being over weight (&lt;span&gt;that being a scaling decrease in the avoidance part of AC as weight goes up.&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;&lt;span&gt;The whole concept of a monk “weight limit” has long been unexplained by &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;SoE&lt;/span&gt; given the modern game and modern itemisation, and especially with recent expansions with even some earrings weighing over 1 each, this is often not a limitation, but rather a huge burden.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Additionally, the weight limit a long time ago was made to scale with level, starting at a base 14, topping out at &amp;lt; 25 at level 60. However, this cap has not changed with the level 65, and level 70 increases as it should in theory have.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Explain the reasoning for the current monk weight limit.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Increase the weight limit cap for level 65 and level 70 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Benifits to being under weight (ie, Additional Innate increase to &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;runspeed&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr size="2" width="100%"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;9. Avoidance&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An increase to avoidance&lt;/strong&gt; - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;font color="#cc0000"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Masters Aura (the &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;PoR&lt;/span&gt; disc, +5%/+10% block/parry/riposte) is currently of minimal use. Overall it has less than a 1.5% increase on misses for monks (and even less for other classes), and with it’s small range means pulling monks are not in range of their group anyway to give them the benefit of the Aura.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Change the Masters Aura &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;PoR&lt;/span&gt; disc to something else useful.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr size="2" width="100%"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;10. FD improvements&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Decrease in Imitate Death timer to be usable for pulling&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Decrease in 2 &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;mins&lt;/span&gt; “stay down” time on FD&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;The Feign Death skill (and Imitate Death, which is a “special” form of FD) could do with some improvements. The refresh timer on Imitate Death (+ Hastened Death) is 24 minutes, which as a pulling tool makes the skill useless. It should be much shorter to enable it to be useful. Additionally the two minute clear agro timer on FD is prohibitively long for pulling.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Fix ID bug so when levitating &amp;amp; moving, using ID does not make the “FD” component fail.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;Change the &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;DoDH&lt;/span&gt; Hastened Death AA to be a larger decrease than 4 &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;mins&lt;/span&gt; per rank. 10 minutes per rank (so down from 6 minutes) &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;(OR) Add an Extended Hastened Death AA that decreases the ID timer further. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Azathool on &lt;span class="date_text"&gt;04-10-2006&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="time_text"&gt;06:47 PM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
