      <description>I don't really think that they need to remove the weight penalty, but I think that they should give monks some sort of reward for staying under it. As it stands now, there is only a penalty (a penalty that is all but pointless for monks over the AC softcap) for going over.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Why not add a reward for staying under 24? Perhaps have it scale, so that staying under 18 or 16 weight would be even better.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It doesn't have to be anything major. Maybe a 1% runspeed boost per 1 weight under the cap? Realistically, the most a monk will be under the cap is maybe 10 weight, and I don't think a 10% runspeed boost would be completely gamebreaking. The vast majority of monks would get 3-6 runspeed boost. Considering that we weigh 1/5 of what most classes do (being very conservative here), I think it would seem even logical.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;That's only an idea. If a dev likes it, great. If a dev has a different idea for a reward, that's cool too. I just want there to be something. It doesn't have to be huge, but just something to encourage monks to adhere by the 'rules' that the devs had in the vision of monks.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
